HEADWORD: Pupillary
<hw>Pu"pil*la*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pupillaris</ets>: cf. F. <ets>pupillaire</ets>. See
<er>Pupil</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to a pupil or
ward.</def> <rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
